▶ {cha' choQmey naQ tu'lu' 'ej tep choQ bIngDaq lo' law' bID choQ tu'lu':sen:nolink} "2 Full Decks and a Half Utility Deck under the Cargo Deck"[2]

This is the plural of {'oH:n:pro}.

Verb prefixes when {bIH:n:nolink} is the subject:
▶ {bIH:n:nolink}:{pagh:n:1h} = {0:v:pref}
▶ {bIH:n:nolink}:{jIH:n:1h} = {mu-:v:pref}
▶ {bIH:n:nolink}:{maH:n:2h} = {nu-:v:pref}
▶ {bIH:n:nolink}:{SoH:n} = {nI-:v:pref}
▶ {bIH:n:nolink}:{tlhIH:n} = {lI-:v:pref}
▶ {bIH:n:nolink}:{ghaH:n}/{'oH:n} = {lu-:v:pref}
▶ {bIH:n:nolink}:{chaH:n}/{bIH:n:nolink} = {0:v:pref}

Verb prefixes when {bIH:n:nolink} is the object:
▶ {jIH:n:1h}:{bIH:n:nolink} = {vI-:v:pref}
▶ {maH:n:2h}:{bIH:n:nolink} = {DI-:v:pref}
▶ {SoH:n}:{bIH:n:nolink} = {Da-:v:pref}
▶ {tlhIH:n}:{bIH:n:nolink} = {bo-:v:pref}
▶ {ghaH:n}/{'oH:n}/{chaH:n}/{bIH:n:nolink}:{bIH:n:nolink} = {0:v:pref}

The imperative verb prefix when {bIH:n:nolink} is the object is {tI-:v:pref}.

