{tlhIngan Hol boQwI':n:nolink} "Klingon Language Assistant" - database version [[VERSION]].

To begin searching, simply type into the search box. On some devices, you may have to press the "Search" (magnifying glass) key or the "Menu" key to activate the search box.

It is recommended to install the {Klingon Keyboard for ASK:url:https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.anysoftkeyboard.languagepack.klingon}. Otherwise, to make it easier to type Klingon on a mobile keyboard, the following shorthand (called "xifan hol") can be enabled under the Preferences menu:
    c ▶ {ch:sen:nolink}
    d ▶ {D:sen:nolink}
    f ▶ {ng:sen:nolink}
    g ▶ {gh:sen:nolink}
    h ▶ {H:sen:nolink}
    i ▶ {I:sen:nolink}
    k ▶ {Q:sen:nolink}
    s ▶ {S:sen:nolink}
    x ▶ {tlh:sen:nolink}
    z ▶ {':sen:nolink}
It is also possible to choose the alternate keymapping:
    k ▶ {q:sen:nolink}
    q ▶ {Q:sen:nolink}

To allow searching directly from the Google search bar, enable {boQwI':n:nolink} in the "Searchable items" list under "Google Search settings".

If you encounter any problems, or have any suggestions, please send me an {email:url:mailto:De.vID.jonpIn@gmail.com?subject=boQwI%27%20feedback&body=Device:%20%0D%0AAndroid%20version:%20%0D%0A}. Please describe the steps to reproduce your problem, along with your device's model and the Android version (both found on your device under Settings ▶ About).

